TITLE: Customizing React Day Picker with Tailwind CSS Classes
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to customize the React Day Picker component using Tailwind CSS classes. Demonstrates using getDefaultClassNames() to extend default styles and applying custom Tailwind classes for today's date, selected day, root element, and navigation chevrons.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gpbl/react-day-picker/blob/main/website/docs/docs/styling.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { DayPicker, getDefaultClassNames } from "react-day-picker";

export function MyCalendar() {
  const defaultClassNames = getDefaultClassNames();
  return (
    <DayPicker
      mode="single"
      classNames={{
        today: `border-amber-500`, // Add a border to today's date
        selected: `bg-amber-500 border-amber-500 text-white`, // Highlight the selected day
        root: `${defaultClassNames.root} shadow-lg p-5`, // Add a shadow to the root element
        chevron: `${defaultClassNames.chevron} fill-amber-500` // Change the color of the chevron
      }}
    />
  );
}
```

