TITLE: Defining DayPickerBase Interface in TypeScript for react-day-picker
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines the DayPickerBase interface, which specifies the props for the DayPicker component. It includes various optional properties for customizing the calendar's appearance and behavior, such as mode, selected, onSelect, fromDate, toDate, and many others.
SOURCE: https://github.com/gpbl/react-day-picker/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-8.10.1/api/interfaces/DayPickerContextValue.md#2025-04-18_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
export interface DayPickerBase {
  /** The initial month to display */
  defaultMonth?: Date;
  /** Function to disable day */
  disableNavigation?: boolean;
  /** Function to disable day */
  disabled?: DateAfter | DayOfWeek[] | Matcher | Matcher[];
  /** The first allowed month (inclusive) */
  fromDate?: Date;
  /** Hide the navigation bar */
  hideHead?: boolean;
  /** Labels for the ARIA attributes */
  labels?: Labels;
  /** The locale(s) to use for formatting dates */
  locale?: Locale | Locale[];
  /** The mode to use the calendar */
  mode?: 'default' | 'multiple' | 'range' | 'single';
  /** Style to apply to the container element */
  style?: CSSProperties;
  /** The last allowed month (inclusive) */
  toDate?: Date;
  /** The number of months displayed */
  numberOfMonths?: number;
  /** The class name to add to the container element */
  className?: string;
  /** Event fired when a day is clicked */
  onDayClick?: DayClickEventHandler;
  /** Event fired when the month changes */
  onMonthChange?: MonthChangeEventHandler;
  /** Event fired when a selection is made */
  onSelect?: SelectEventHandler;
  /** The initial selected day(s) */
  selected?: Date | Date[] | DateRange | undefined;
  /** Render function for the footer */
  footer?: React.ReactNode | ((currentMonth: Date) => React.ReactNode);
  // ... (other properties)
}
```

